---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// SEO: Schema de Evento para que Google entienda las fechas clave
const scheduleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SportsEvent",
  "name": "FIFA World Cup 2026 Tournament Schedule",
  "startDate": "2026-06-11",
  "endDate": "2026-07-19",
  "eventStatus": "https://schema.org/EventScheduled",
  "description": "The complete timeline and key dates for the 2026 World Cup in North America."
};
---

<Layout 
  title="FIFA World Cup 2026 Schedule & Key Dates" 
  description="Mark your calendar. Full timeline, opening match details, and the complete schedule for the 2026 World Cup in the USA, Mexico, and Canada."
  schema={scheduleSchema}
>
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-black mb-6 text-blue-900 tracking-tight">2026 World Cup Schedule: The Road to the Final</h1>
  
  <article class="prose lg:prose-lg max-w-none mb-12 text-gray-700">
    <p>Forty-eight teams, three host nations, and 104 matches. The 2026 tournament is a logistical beast, and keeping track of the timeline is crucial if you're planning to travel or just want to organize your watch parties.</p>
    
    <p>We've broken down the master schedule so you know exactly when the critical phases of the tournament kick off. The expansion means a longer tournament, stretching over a thrilling 39 days.</p>
  </article>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg">June 11, 2026</div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">The Opening Match</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-600">The historic Estadio Azteca in Mexico City gets the honor of kicking off the tournament. It will become the first stadium in history to host three World Cup opening matches. Expect a massive celebration and the host nation, Mexico, taking the pitch.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg">June 11 - June 27</div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Group Stage Window</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-600">With 12 groups of four teams, this period will be absolute football chaos. There will be up to four matches a day during the peak of this phase. Regional clustering will be used heavily here to minimize travel fatigue for the squads.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="bg-red-600 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg">June 28 - July 19</div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">The Knockout Gauntlet</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-600">The introduction of the Round of 32 means an extra knockout hurdle for the contenders. The stakes get higher as teams navigate the Round of 16, Quarter-finals, and Semi-finals, culminating in the ultimate showdown on July 19 at MetLife Stadium in New Jersey.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>